Categories: Structured Text Processing -> Operation on Primitives -> Numbers -> List
Definition: In this task, you will be given a list of integers. You should remove all of the odd integers from the list(consider 0 an even number). If every integer in the input list is odd then an empty list ("[]") should be returned. Otherwise, answer with the list of even numbers separated by comma inside brackets.

Positive Examples.explanation: 1 and 9 are removed from the list because they are odd numbers.
Every value in the input list is odd so an empty list is returned.
-3 and -31 are removed from the list, because they are odd numbers.

Negative Examples.explanation: The output contains only the odd numbers from the input.
The output only included one instance of the element 8, even though it appears two times in the input list.
Your given numbers should be in brackets.
